%% Sequence of a fluent, consuming-self builder
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Caller
    participant B as HttpClientBuilder
    participant C as HttpClient

    Caller->>C: HttpClient::builder()
    C-->>Caller: HttpClientBuilder { None, None, None }

    Caller->>B: .endpoint("https://api.example.com")
    Note right of B: self is moved in,<br/>new Self moved out
    B-->>Caller: HttpClientBuilder (chained)

    Caller->>B: .timeout(Duration::from_secs(5))
    B-->>Caller: HttpClientBuilder (chained)

    Caller->>B: .retries(3)
    B-->>Caller: HttpClientBuilder (chained)

    Caller->>B: .build()
    alt all required fields set & valid
        B->>C: construct HttpClient { ... }
        C-->>Caller: Ok(HttpClient)
    else missing or invalid field
        B-->>Caller: Err(BuildError)
        Note right of Caller: use ? to propagate,<br/>never .unwrap()
    end
